# ArgoCD-Based Service Discovery

## Discovery Contract

`ArgoCDObserver` (`src/observers/argocd.py`) is the **only** supported discovery, health,
and sync mechanism. It watches ArgoCD Application CRs cluster-wide via the K8s Watch API
(`argoproj.io/v1alpha1/applications`) -- the `/telemetry` push endpoint returns HTTP 410,
and the old `darwin.io/*` pod-annotation scanning (`KubernetesObserver`) has been removed.

## Extraction Model

Each ArgoCD Application explodes into N Darwin services -- one per `Deployment` entry in
`status.resources[]`:

| Source Field | Darwin Service Field | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| `resource.name` | `Service.name` | Direct match; `ARGOCD_NAME_MAPPING` env var reserved for mismatches |
| `resource.namespace` (or Application namespace) | `Service.namespace` | |
| `resource.health.status` | `Service.health_status` | Healthy, Progressing, Degraded, Missing, Unknown |
| `resource.status` | `Service.sync_status` | Synced, OutOfSync, Unknown |
| `spec.source.repoURL` | `Service.gitops_repo_url` | Application-level -- shared by every exploded service |
| `spec.source.path` | `Service.gitops_config_path` | Application-level |
| `status.summary.images[0]` (tag) | `Service.version` | First image tag; coarse-grained by design |
| `status.operationState` + `status.history[]` | `Service.last_operations` | Current op + last 5 history entries |

**Accepted limitation (from probe):** replica counts are NOT available in
`status.resources[]` -- graceful degradation via ArgoCD `health.status=Degraded` (which
implicitly covers "replicas not ready") instead of a separate replica-count signal.

## Health Model

`calculate_health_from_argocd(health_status, sync_status, last_seen)` in `blackboard.py`
is the sole health calculation:

- `Healthy`/`Progressing` + `Synced` -> `healthy`
- `Healthy`/`Progressing` + `OutOfSync` -> `warning`
- `Degraded` -> `critical`
- `Missing`/`Unknown`, or `last_seen` beyond `ZOMBIE_THRESHOLD` (90s) -> `unknown`

## OutOfSync Alerting Gate

Aligner (`handle_sync_drift`) only escalates OutOfSync when `spec.syncPolicy.automated`
exists on the Application AND the drift persists beyond a 60s dwell time. Applications
without `automated` sync are expected to sit OutOfSync (manual workflow) -- never alert.

## Constants (source of truth)

Defined in `src/observers/argocd.py`:

- `ARGOCD_OBSERVER_ENABLED`, `ARGOCD_GROUP`, `ARGOCD_VERSION`, `ARGOCD_PLURAL`
- `ARGOCD_NAME_MAPPING` (env var, JSON string) -- resource-name -> service-name overrides

## Consumed By

- `ArgoCDObserver._extract_and_update()` -- writes `Service.health_status`/`sync_status`/
  `namespace`/`argocd_app`/`last_operations` (via `update_service_argocd_status()`) and
  `version`/`gitops_repo_url`/`gitops_config_path` (via `update_service_discovery()`)
- Blackboard topology graph (`get_graph_data()`) -- namespace-grouped nodes, no dependency edges
- Aligner (`handle_health_change`, `handle_sync_drift`) -- deterministic escalation, no LLM in the loop
